'''Cobbler(s)''' may refer to: {{TOC right}}
==Places== * [[The Cobbler]], a mountain located near the head of Loch Long in Scotland * [[Cobbler, Missouri]], a community in the United States
==Art, entertainment and media== * [[The Cobbler (1923 film)|''The Cobbler'' (1923 film)]], a short comedy by Hal Roach * [[The Cobbler (2014 film)|''The Cobbler'' (2014 film)]], a comedy-drama starring Adam Sandler * [[Cobbler (Better Call Saul)|"Cobbler" (''Better Call Saul'')]], an episode of the TV series ''Better Call Saul'' * "The Cunning Cobbler", a folk song, No. 174 in the [[Roud Folk Song Index]], also called "The Cunning Cobbler Done Over"
==Fish== * Cobbler or river cobbler, a marketing name in the UK for Southeast Asian [[Pangasius bocourti]] and [[Pangasius pangasius]] (also marketed as "[[Basa fish|basa]]", "pangasius" and "panga") * Cobbler, a common name for ''[[Cnidoglanis macrocephalus]]'', a species of catfish found along the coasts of Australia * Cobbler, a common name for the [[South Australian cobbler]], a brown fish found in estuaries in southern Australia
==Food and drink== * [[Cobbler (food)]], a type of pie * Cobbler, a type of [[mixed drink]] made with wine or sherry, citrus juice and sugar
==Occupations== * Cobbler, a person who [[Shoemaking|repairs, and sometimes makes, shoes]] * Cobbler, a person who illegally forges [[fake passport|passports]] and other documents
==Other uses== * [[Cobbler (software)]], a network-oriented install server for Linux * {{ship|USS|Cobbler}}, a United States Navy ship name ** {{ship|USS|Cobbler|SS-344}}, a former submarine in the United States Navy * "The Cobblers", a nickname for the English association football club [[Northampton Town F.C.]] * [[Load of old cobblers|Cobblers]], a slang term for nonsense; see [[Rhyming slang#Taboo terms]]
